<section>
<title>Detailed Description</title>

<para>The base class for all fingers.</para>

<para>This class serves as the interface between the HandController object, the parent <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_hand">Hand</link> object and the concrete finger objects.</para>

<para>Subclasses of <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_unity_1_1_finger_model">FingerModel</link> must implement <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_unity_1_1_finger_model_1a27b24f96e9e709625779cc24bd5d72f3">InitFinger()</link> and <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_unity_1_1_finger_model_1a9103f063172a8f99a9aa083407ada2a2">UpdateFinger()</link>. The InitHand() function is typically called by the parent <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_unity_1_1_hand_model">HandModel</link> InitHand() method; likewise, the <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_unity_1_1_finger_model_1a9103f063172a8f99a9aa083407ada2a2">UpdateFinger()</link> function is typically called by the parent <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_unity_1_1_hand_model">HandModel</link> UpdateHand() function. </para>
